<h2 id="tweets-vectorization">Tweets vectorization</h2>

<p>Alright, we now know that our models won‚Äôt accept more than numeric values. This is the reason why we need to convert all tweets into this kind of values, and the best way is through a vectorizer such as CountVectorizer or TFIDF Vectorizer. I implemented TFIDF Vectorizer which is known by deliver good results. Let‚Äôs introduce some theory about it:</p>

<p>One of the best approaches when working with text data is to rescale features by how informative we expect them to be. One of the most common ways to do this is using the term frequency‚Äìinverse document frequency (tf‚Äìidf) method. The intuition of this method is to give high weight to any term that appears often in a particular document, but not in many documents in the corpus. If a word appears often in a particular document, but not in very many documents, it is likely to be very descriptive of the content of that document.</p>

<p>Once we have our text transformed as numeric features, it‚Äôs time to apply Clustering techniques:</p>

